From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] leds: add Google Nexus Q (steelhead) AVR LED ring driver

Add the steelhead-AVR LED ring + keys driver for the Google Nexus Q
(codename steelhead). The AVR MCU on i2c2 drives 32 RGB ring LEDs plus a
mute LED and reports the capacitive mute/volume keys.

Registers a multicolor LED class device per LED (mute + 32 ring), a
"frame" binary sysfs attribute for whole-ring updates, and an input
device for the keys. Includes KUnit tests for the pure-logic encode/
decode helpers.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
 drivers/leds/Kconfig                   |  14 +
 drivers/leds/Makefile                  |   2 +
 drivers/leds/leds-steelhead-avr-test.c |  58 ++++
 drivers/leds/leds-steelhead-avr.c      | 472 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 drivers/leds/steelhead_avr.h           |  50 ++++
 5 files changed, 596 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/leds/leds-steelhead-avr-test.c
